bar, a part, portion, lot, or pari, anything which happens fortuitously
or fortunately; whence the annual festival in commemoration of the
wonderful deliverance of the Jews from their enemies was called Purim,
or in Arabic and Persian, Fuhr, or Lots; which has been observed by
them, in all places of their dispersion, from that day to the present
time, without any interruption. [Est
